  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Taijutsu (Strike)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 12 (Spell Level 6)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 15</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 27 | <b>Successes:</b> 4</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 15 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 29</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> E, H</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>This advanced form of Risai Butsu exerts such power that the target's chest cavity looks like it might cave in. This technique functions as Juuryu: Risai Butsu, except as noted above, and the attack instead deals unarmed damage as though you were two size categories larger, plus 2 per Strength Rank you currently benefit from. If hit, the target also suffers 1d6 damage per two levels (10d6 maximum; Fortitude halves).</p>\n\n\n<p><b>Mastery:</b> The third step has the target fall @Condition[prone]{prone} if they fail their Fortitude save.<br><br>The fifth step increases the bonus damage by 2d6, and increases the maximum bonus damage to 12d6.</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
